Not sure  where to go from here.  I thought I remembered
someone mentioning  drilling and tapping the steering wheel, but I can't find
anything about it  in the archives.  Any ideas would be appreciated.



Best  regards,



Mark
hey Mark That would have been me.  We  will sometimes drill 2 holes on the 
sides of the nut and tap the holes   start with 6mm and if need be go to 8 mm  
then use a crows foot puller to  remove the wheel.  It helps top leave the nut 
on at the top of the  threads so as not to mess up the threads. I have seen 
the factory puller and  it goes from the top around to the bottom of the wheel 
and kinda pushes the  wheel off.  later  mark  d





